your torso directly under your bust, where 00:00:12.379 --> 00:00:14.280
your bra band is. 00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:18.720
If this measurement is even, add 4 to get your band size.
00:00:18.720 --> 00:00:21.890 If it’s odd, add 5 instead.
00:00:21.890 --> 00:00:25.800 Next, measure loosely around the fullest part
of your bust. 00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:29.279
Make sure the measuring tape is level with the ground.
00:00:29.279 --> 00:00:34.660 Once you have both numbers, subtract your
band size from the cup measurement you took 00:00:34.660 --> 00:00:36.660
to get your cup size. 00:00:36.660 --> 00:00:44.030
If the difference is less than 1 inch (2 1/2 cm), your cup size is AA.
00:00:44.030 --> 00:00:54.760 If the difference is 1 inch (2 1/2 cm), your
cup size is A. Two inches (5 cm) is B, 3 inches 00:00:54.760 --> 00:01:08.920
(7 1/2 cm) is C, 4 inches (10 cm) is D, 5
inches (12 1/2 cm) if DD, 6 inches (15 cm) 00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:14.250
is F, and 7 inches (18 cm) is G.

00:00:00.470 --> 00:00:07.419 The goal of Blackjack is to have a hand that
totals higher than the dealer’s, but doesn’t 00:00:07.419 --> 00:00:10.660
total to higher than 21. 00:00:10.660 --> 00:00:17.189
If your hand totals higher than 21, it is
called a “bust”, which means you are out 00:00:17.189 --> 00:00:20.029
of the game. 00:00:20.029 --> 00:00:24.949
The game starts with everyone besides the dealer placing a bet.
00:00:24.949 --> 00:00:36.710 Then, the dealer deals 1 card face up to each
player and 1 card face up to themselves. 00:00:36.710 --> 00:00:43.080
Everyone is dealt one more face-up card besides
the dealer, whose second card is dealt face 00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:47.300 down.
00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:55.330 Cards 2 through 10 are scored using their
face value, and Jacks, Queens, and Kings are 00:00:55.330 --> 00:00:58.820
all equal to 10. 00:00:58.820 --> 00:01:06.720
Aces can be either 1 or 10, and you can choose
their value throughout the round if you have 00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:09.750 one.
00:01:09.750 --> 00:01:16.400
If your two face-up cards total 21, you automatically
win one and a half times your bet from the 00:01:16.400 --> 00:01:20.830
dealer, and you’re done for that round. 00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:28.110
Otherwise, the dealer asks whether you want
another card from the top of the deck. 00:01:28.110 --> 00:01:33.640
If you do, say “hit” or motion toward yourself with your hand.
00:01:33.640 --> 00:01:39.800 There’s no limit to how many cards you can
ask for, but once your hand totals higher 00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:44.910
than 21, you bust and the dealer gets your bet. 00:01:44.910 --> 00:01:54.340
If you don’t want any more cards, say “stay” or wave your hand over the table.
00:01:54.340 --> 00:02:00.770 Once the dealer has gone around the table,
they flip up their face-down card. 00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:06.480
If it’s 16 or under, they have to take another card.

00:00:00.280 --> 00:00:05.600 Before you get started playing any type of
5-card poker, you’ll need to learn the 10 00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:08.330
basic ways to win. 00:00:08.330 --> 00:00:12.410
In order from lowest to highest, they are: 00:00:12.410 --> 00:00:13.999 1.
00:00:13.999 --> 00:00:15.540 High card. 00:00:15.540 --> 00:00:16.700 2.
00:00:16.700 --> 00:00:21.390 Pair of cards, like two 2s. 3.
00:00:21.390 --> 00:00:27.630 Two pairs of cards, like two 5s and two 9s. 4.
00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:32.700 Three of a kind, like three 4s. 5.
00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:37.960 Straight, which is five cards in sequential order.
00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:46.340 For example, a player might have a 3, 4, 5,
6, and 7 of any suit. 00:00:46.340 --> 00:00:47.839 6.
00:00:47.839 --> 00:00:53.570 Flush, which is when a player has five cards
of the same suit in any order. 00:00:53.570 --> 00:01:03.059
For example, a player might have a 2, 7, 10, Jack, and Queen of spades.
00:01:03.059 --> 00:01:04.280 7. 00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:10.830
Full house, which is when a player has a pair and a three of a kind.
00:01:10.830 --> 00:01:12.049 8. 00:01:12.049 --> 00:01:16.380
Four of a kind, like all four Aces. 00:01:16.380 --> 00:01:18.299 9.
00:01:18.299 --> 00:01:24.149 Straight flush, which is when you have five
cards in sequential order of the same suit. 00:01:24.149 --> 00:01:32.740
For example, a player might have a 5, 6, 7, 8, and 9 of clubs.
00:01:32.740 --> 00:01:34.220 10. 00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:48.490
Royal Flush, which is a straight flush containing
a 10, Jack, Queen, King, and Ace. 00:01:48.490 --> 00:01:54.000
If two people have the same hand, the person with the higher cards wins.
00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:02.210 So for example, if Daniel has a pair of 3s
and Maggie has a pair of 10s, Maggie wins 00:02:02.210 --> 00:02:07.340
because her pair is higher. 00:02:07.340 --> 00:02:12.480
To play Texas Hold’Em, which is the most common type of poker, you’ll first need
00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:18.610 to bet your “ante,” which is your “buy
in bet” to play the round. 00:02:18.610 --> 00:02:27.480
The ante is usually a small bet, like $1 or $5, and it’s decided by the table.
00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:33.290 Once everyone has their ante, the dealer will
deal two cards to each player. 00:02:33.290 --> 00:02:36.590
Keep these cards secret from everyone else. 00:02:36.590 --> 00:02:44.660
Now, every player will take a look at their
cards and choose whether or not to bet. 00:02:44.660 --> 00:02:49.769
Whenever there’s a betting round, you can
choose to “fold,” which means not playing 00:02:49.769 --> 00:02:57.790
this round, “check,” which means matching
their bet, or “raise,” which means adding 00:02:57.790 --> 00:03:02.890
more money to the betting pool. 00:03:02.890 --> 00:03:08.280
Players that are unwilling to “check”
a bet have to fold; and if everyone but one 00:03:08.280 --> 00:03:12.930
player “folds,” that player wins! 00:03:12.930 --> 00:03:18.489
Once everyone has bet, the dealer will reveal three cards.
00:03:18.489 --> 00:03:22.480 These cards are known as the “flop.”
00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:28.080 When you see the flop, start planning what
hand you want to make, keeping in mind that 00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:31.459
there are still two more cards to be revealed. 00:03:31.459 --> 00:03:38.720
For example, you might want to aim for a flush,
which is when you have five cards of the same 00:03:38.720 --> 00:03:42.810
suit. 00:03:42.810 --> 00:03:50.250 After the flop, everyone has the chance to
bet again, before the dealer reveals the next 00:03:50.250 --> 00:03:56.099
card, which is the “turn.” 00:03:56.099 --> 00:04:03.569
Bet again if you want to, then the dealer will reveal the “river,” which is the
00:04:03.569 --> 00:04:06.409 last card. 00:04:06.409 --> 00:04:15.760
At this point, you’ll see a total of 7 cards:
two in your hands, and five on the table. 00:04:15.760 --> 00:04:29.190
Now, players will bet once last time, then everyone will reveal their hand.
00:04:29.190 --> 00:04:35.389 Your goal is to create the highest hand possible
out of those seven cards, even if it means 00:04:35.389 --> 00:04:44.150
only using one card from your hand and four cards from the table.
00:04:44.150 --> 00:04:47.000 The player with the best hand wins!

plus C where a and B and C are the lengths of the sides of the triangle for

is 15 if you only know the lengths of two of the triangle sides you can still
find the perimeter if it's a right triangle which means the triangle has

would add 3 plus 4 plus 5 and get 12 therefore the perimeter of the triangle
is 12

00:00:00.250 --> 00:00:05.540 Registering to vote in most U.S. states is
a quick and easy process. 00:00:05.540 --> 00:00:11.480
To be eligible to vote, you must be a U.S.
citizen, and at least 18 years old by election 00:00:11.480 --> 00:00:12.480
day. 00:00:12.480 --> 00:00:17.640 If you are under the age of 18, you may be
able to pre-register to vote if allowed by 00:00:17.640 --> 00:00:19.960
your state’s laws. 00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:24.689
If you are a first-time voter, you will need
to provide proof of identity when registering 00:00:24.689 --> 00:00:30.150
such as a driver’s license, state ID, or passport. 00:00:30.150 --> 00:00:35.540
You may also need to provide additional proof
of residence such as a current utility bill 00:00:35.540 --> 00:00:37.470
or bank statement. 00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:42.980
Check your State Election Office website for a list of acceptable documents.
00:00:42.980 --> 00:00:47.260 Note that there may be additional eligibility
requirements for your state. 00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:53.570
For example, some states may not allow those
with former felony convictions to vote. 00:00:53.570 --> 00:01:00.280
You can learn more about your state's requirements
by visiting your State Election Office website. 00:01:00.280 --> 00:01:04.780
If you meet your state’s requirements, you’re ready to register.
00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:11.850
There are three ways you can submit your registration:
in person, by mail, or online. 00:01:11.850 --> 00:01:17.770
You can register to vote in person at your
local or state election office, or at the 00:01:17.770 --> 00:01:21.890
DMV if your state has what is known as a “motor voter law.”
00:01:21.890 --> 00:01:28.470 You can register by mail by using a National
Mail Voter Registration Form or via your state’s 00:01:28.470 --> 00:01:31.130
voter registration form. 00:01:31.130 --> 00:01:36.550
If you don't have access to a computer, you
can pick up a registration form at many government 00:01:36.550 --> 00:01:43.580
offices, such as the Post Office, your local DMV, or a public library.
00:01:43.580 --> 00:01:47.560 In several states, you can also register to
vote online. 00:01:47.560 --> 00:01:55.229
Currently, 39 states plus the District of Columbia offer online registration.
00:01:55.229 --> 00:02:00.360 If you plan on voting in an upcoming election,
make sure to register to vote before your 00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:02.100
state’s deadline. 00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:06.180
You can find your state’s voter registration
deadline, as well as same-day registration 00:02:06.180 --> 00:02:15.300
details on your State Election Office website
or a nonprofit, nonpartisan website like Vote.org. 00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:25.200
The earliest state deadline for the 2020 presidential
election is October 3, 2020. 00:02:25.200 --> 00:02:30.709
If you miss the registration deadline, your
state may offer same-day registration in-person 00:02:30.709 --> 00:02:35.040
during early voting as well as at polling centers on Election Day.

business finances can be a little complicated but once you've got the
basic concepts down you'll be well on your way to successfully managing your
business's income and expenses one of the first concepts you'll want to be
familiar with is revenue revenue is the total dollar amount that your business
earns in a given time period before subtracting expenses imagine you run a
lemonade stand and you sell 100 glasses of lemonade for $1 per glass in a month
your revenue for that month would be $100 not all of that money goes into
your pocket though you also need to factor in the cost of goods sold or cogs
for short cogs is the amount you spend on materials in labor to produce your
goods or services for your lemonade stand your cogs would include the cost

00:01
of sugar lemons and cups if you need 50 lemons 100 cups and 25 cups of sugar to
make 100 glasses of lemonade and lemons are 25 cents each cups are ten cents
each and cups of sugar are 15 cents each your cogs would be 26 dollars and 25
cents once you know your cogs you can calculate the gross profit for your
business gross profit is the amount of money your business brings in in any
given time period your revenue minus the cost of goods sold with the revenue for
your lemonade stand at $100 in the cogs at $26.25 the gross profit for your
business would be $100 minus twenty six dollars and twenty five cents or seventy
three dollars and seventy five cents however you still need to calculate one
more thing to determine how much of that

00:02
money will be going into your pocket and that's net profit net profit also known
as your bottom-line is the amount of money your business earns in any given
time period minus expenses and the cost of goods sold
for your lemonade stand your expenses might include printing posters to
advertise your stand paying a friend to help you pass out the posters and buying
a wagon to carry your supplies say all of these expenses add up to $30 to
calculate net profit you would subtract your $30 expenses from your gross profit
which is seventy three dollars and seventy five cents that would leave you
with forty three dollars and seventy five cents in net profit which you can
put into your pocket or reinvest in your business something else you should keep
in mind is your gross margin gross margin is the percentage of every dollar
you make that is gross profit the higher your gross margin the more profit you

00:03
make with each sale to calculate gross margin just subtract your cogs from your
revenue and divide that number by your revenue for your lemonade stand you
would subtract the cost of goods sold or cogs $26.25 from your revenue 100
dollars and then divide by that same revenue the gross margin for your
lemonade stand would be seventy three percent meaning seventy three percent of
every dollar you take in is gross profit to keep track of all of these different
numbers as a business you'll want to use an income statement an income statement
also called a profit and loss statement shows the revenue expenses and net
profit for your business in a given period of time your lemonade stands
income statement would show how much you spent how much you earned and what your

00:04
net profit or loss for the month is similarly you'll want to have a balance
sheet a balance sheet shows the financial status of your business at a
given time including your assets or things your business owns that are of
value and liabilities which are your financial debts and obligations
for your lemonade stand the balance sheet would include things like how much
cash is in your register and the wooden stand you own which are both assets as
well as the monthly payments you're making on the wagon which is a liability
your balance sheet can be used to determine how financially healthy your
business's a financially healthy business will have more assets than
liabilities another concept you should be familiar with is cash flow cash flow
is the movement of money in and out of your business within a 1 month period

00:05
its measured by comparing the amount of money your business has available at the
beginning of the month to cash available
at the end of the month you can use your cash flow to determine when to spend
more money on your business for example you might buy more supplies for your
lemonade stand at the beginning of the month when you have more cash on hand
finally you'll need to understand how accounts receivable and accounts payable
work accounts receivable is money that's owed to your business say your lemonade
stand offers a promotion where customers can pay a monthly rate for unlimited
lemonade in that case those monthly payments would be included in your
accounts receivable their accounts payable on the other hand is money that
your business owes to its creditors if you have lemons delivered daily from a
local farm for your lemonade stand your monthly lemon bill would be
included in your accounts payable now that you understand the basics of
business finances you're ready to manage your money and grow your business

00:00:00.399 --> 00:00:06.020 To pick a lock with a bobby pin, first bend
open a bobby pin until it makes a 90-degree 00:00:06.020 --> 00:00:09.490
angle, and remove the rubber piece on the straight end.
00:00:09.490 --> 00:00:13.659 Make a slight bend at the tip of the straight end.
00:00:13.659 --> 00:00:21.130 Now, take a second bobby pin and bend the
closed end to one side so it forms a 90-degree 00:00:21.130 --> 00:00:22.130
angle. 00:00:22.130 --> 00:00:25.660 You’ll use this bobby pin as a lever.
00:00:25.660 --> 00:00:30.499 Insert the bent end of the lever into the
lock, and turn the lever to one side to apply 00:00:30.499 --> 00:00:31.960
tension. 00:00:31.960 --> 00:00:37.790
Next, insert the bent end of the pick into the lock above the lever.
00:00:37.790 --> 00:00:42.710 There are 5 pins inside of a standard lock,
and each pin needs to be pressed up to the 00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:46.190
same point for the lock to open. 00:00:46.190 --> 00:00:50.960
You can use the end of the pick to press the
pins up, but you’ll need to start with the 00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:52.640
pin that’s seized. 00:00:52.640 --> 00:00:56.580
A seized pin is a pin that’s harder to press up than the rest.
00:00:56.580 --> 00:01:02.570 To find the seized pin, start near the outside
of the lock and press up on each pin one at 00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:08.250
a time, inserting the pick further and further into the lock as you go.
00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:11.380 When you feel resistance, you’ve found a
seized pin. 00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.330
Now, move the pick up and down to force the seized pin up.
00:01:16.330 --> 00:01:20.580 Keep doing this until you hear an audible click.
00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:24.060 Make sure you’re still applying pressure
with the lever. 00:01:24.060 --> 00:01:28.780
This pressure will cause the lock to turn
slightly when the seized pin is pushed up. 00:01:28.780 --> 00:01:35.520
Next, find another seized pin the same way
you did before, and repeat the process. 00:01:35.520 --> 00:01:40.550
Every time a seized pin is freed, another
pin will become seized, so there will always 00:01:40.550 --> 00:01:43.110
be a seized pin to press up. 00:01:43.110 --> 00:01:47.979
Continue pressing the seized pins up with
the pick until you’ve lifted up every pin 00:01:47.979 --> 00:01:49.390
and the lock unlocks.

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.450 Backgammon is a 2-player board game that is
played on a backgammon board, which is a board 00:00:05.450 --> 00:00:13.829
divided in the middle with 12 triangular spaces,
called points, in each quadrant. 00:00:13.829 --> 00:00:19.769
Each player sits on opposite sides of the
board and has 15 color-coded checker pieces 00:00:19.769 --> 00:00:21.689
to play with. 00:00:21.689 --> 00:00:27.169
The goal of the game is to be the first to
remove all of your pieces off of the board, 00:00:27.169 --> 00:00:29.940
which is also called “bearing off.” 00:00:29.940 --> 00:00:35.860
To set the game up, the first player sets
3 pieces up in a vertical row at the base 00:00:35.860 --> 00:00:42.930
of the fifth point from their left, in the
bottom half of the board, and 5 pieces in 00:00:42.930 --> 00:00:47.350
the first point directly to the bottom right of the board’s partition.
00:00:47.350 --> 00:00:54.449 Then, that player lines up 5 pieces at the
left-most point at the top left, and 2 pieces 00:00:54.449 --> 00:00:58.739
in the last point on the top right. 00:00:58.739 --> 00:01:04.160
The opposing player sets their color’s pieces
up to mirror their opponent’s pieces, so 00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:11.090
that each row of 2 has a mirror row of 2 on
the opposite side, each row of 3 has a mirror 00:01:11.090 --> 00:01:13.740
row of 3, and so on. 00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:19.729
The first player’s pieces are only allowed
to move counterclockwise, starting in the 00:01:19.729 --> 00:01:22.170
top right. 00:01:22.170 --> 00:01:27.630
The second player’s pieces are only allowed
to move clockwise, starting at the top on 00:01:27.630 --> 00:01:30.000
their left. 00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:38.590
To start play, players take alternating turns rolling 2 6-sided dice.
00:01:38.590 --> 00:01:44.340 For each of the numbers that gets rolled,
the rolling player moves 1 or 2 pieces based 00:01:44.340 --> 00:01:47.719
on the numbers rolled on the dice. 00:01:47.719 --> 00:01:54.969
So a roll of a 5 and 2 would allow the rolling
player to move one piece 2 points and another 00:01:54.969 --> 00:01:57.820
piece 5 points. 00:01:57.820 --> 00:02:03.140
Alternatively, that player may move 1 piece 7 points.
00:02:03.140 --> 00:02:05.812 Rolling 2 of the same number allows that player
to move 4 times. 00:02:05.812 --> 00:02:15.190
For example, a roll of 2 and 2 allows that
player to move a total of 8 points, although 00:02:15.190 --> 00:02:20.220
each piece being moved must travel 2 points at a time.
00:02:20.220 --> 00:02:26.010 Players cannot move a piece to a point that
is occupied by 2 or more of their opponent’s 00:02:26.010 --> 00:02:32.360
pieces, but may stack their own pieces on a single point.
00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:37.750 If a player moves a piece to a point with
only 1 of their opponent’s pieces on it, 00:02:37.750 --> 00:02:41.170
that opposing player’s piece is removed
from the board and placed on the middle partition. 00:02:41.170 --> 00:02:44.230
At the beginning of the next player’s turn,
they must use at least 1 of their rolls to 00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:49.570
remove that piece from the partition and start
it over from the beginning point on their 00:02:49.570 --> 00:02:51.980
side of the board. 00:02:51.980 --> 00:02:57.060
Once all of a player’s pieces are in the
quadrant of the board closest to the end, 00:02:57.060 --> 00:03:01.640
that player may begin removing pieces off of the board.
00:03:01.640 --> 00:03:06.780 Once a player moves a piece 1 point past the
edge of the board, it is removed from the 00:03:06.780 --> 00:03:08.050 game.
00:03:08.050 --> 00:03:12.050 A player wins once all of their pieces are
removed from the board.

Then, remove a new mask from the box and make
sure there aren’t any tears or holes in 00:00:11.090 --> 00:00:12.259 it.
00:00:12.259 --> 00:00:16.750 Locate the top edge of the mask, which is
the stiff, bendable edge that can be molded 00:00:16.750 --> 00:00:18.740
to fit your nose. 00:00:18.740 --> 00:00:23.279
Make sure the colored side of the mask is
facing outwards and the white side is facing 00:00:23.279 --> 00:00:24.730
towards you. 00:00:24.730 --> 00:00:30.419
Then, place the mask on your face so it’s covering your nose and mouth.
00:00:30.419 --> 00:00:35.180 If the mask has 2 ear loops on either side
of it, wrap these around your ears to hold 00:00:35.180 --> 00:00:36.810
the mask in place. 00:00:36.810 --> 00:00:42.130
If the mask has ties on it, position the top
ties over the crown of your head and tie a 00:00:42.130 --> 00:00:44.590
bow to secure them. 00:00:44.590 --> 00:00:50.480
Then, do the same thing with the bottom ties at the nape of your neck.
00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:56.320 For a mask with bands, pull the top band over
your head so it rests on the crown of your 00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:57.320 head.
00:00:57.320 --> 00:01:03.100 Then, pull the bottom band over your head
so it rests on the nape of your neck. 00:01:03.100 --> 00:01:08.380
Mold the stiff edge at the top of the mask
to your nose, and pull the bottom of the mask 00:01:08.380 --> 00:01:13.079
down so it’s covering your mouth and chin. 00:01:13.079 --> 00:01:17.390
When you’re ready to remove your medical
mask, wash your hands with soap and water 00:01:17.390 --> 00:01:19.850
or hand sanitizer first. 00:01:19.850 --> 00:01:25.130
Then, remove the mask using the ear loops, ties, or bands.
00:01:25.130 --> 00:01:28.990 Avoid touching the front of the mask since
it could be contaminated. 00:01:28.990 --> 00:01:34.429
Finally, throw the used mask in the trash and wash your hands one more time.

00:00:00.399 --> 00:00:07.799 To play solitaire, try to get all of the cards
into 4 foundation piles, 1 pile per suit, 00:00:07.799 --> 00:00:16.270
in ascending order from ace to king. Once
you finish all 4 foundation piles, you win! 00:00:16.270 --> 00:00:23.859
To set up the game, first place 1 card face
up and 6 cards face down to the right. Repeat 00:00:23.859 --> 00:00:36.020
until every column has a face-up card at the
bottom. Place the remaining cards in a pile 00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:42.920
off to the side. To start the game, look at
the face-up cards to see if you can move any 00:00:42.920 --> 00:00:49.470
of them to access the face-down cards underneath.
You can move a face-up card to the bottom 00:00:49.470 --> 00:00:55.390
of another column if the face-up card you’re
playing it on is a different color and one 00:00:55.390 --> 00:01:01.420
number higher than it. When you move a face-up
card and expose a face-down card underneath 00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:08.540
it, turn the face-down card over. If you have
a face-up ace, place it above the playing 00:01:08.540 --> 00:01:15.740
area to start one of the 4 foundation piles
you need to win the game. Then, when you encounter 00:01:15.740 --> 00:01:22.370
the 2 in that suit, play it on top of the
ace, followed by the 3 in that suit, and so 00:01:22.370 --> 00:01:30.860
on. Continue to move the face-up cards around
the playing area and into the 4 suit piles. 00:01:30.860 --> 00:01:35.810
Once you come to a point where you can’t
move any more cards, flip over the top 3 cards 00:01:35.810 --> 00:01:42.520
from the reserve pile, and see if you can
play the top card anywhere. If you can, play 00:01:42.520 --> 00:01:49.120
it and then see if you can play the card underneath
it. If you can’t, flip over 3 more cards 00:01:49.120 --> 00:01:55.400
from the reserve pile. Whenever you are stuck,
you can continue flipping over sets of 3 cards 00:01:55.400 --> 00:02:01.920
from the reserve pile as long as you’d like,
but make sure to never shuffle it. Keep playing 00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:06.729
like this until you’ve moved all of the
cards into the corresponding suit piles in 00:02:06.729 --> 00:02:10.204
ascending order, or have run out of cards
that you are able to move. You can move cards 00:02:10.204 --> 00:02:10.619
around, but they can only go on cards that
are 1 number higher and the opposite color.

if you don't already know it you can estimate the volume

germs and combined chlorine which is chlorine that's already been used up

pool water as they dissolve replace the tablets often enough
to maintain a free chlorine level of 1 to 3 ppm

which prevents uv rays from breaking down the chlorine as quickly
you'll also need to buy cyanuric acid dilute it
and add it to the pool according to the instructions to stabilize the chlorine
you should maintain a cyanuric acid level of about 50 ppm in the pool
in addition to routine chlorination you'll also need to shock the pool water
